In this op-ed, President Obama reflects on the impact of Title IX, a law that bans gender discrimination in public schools. He mentions coaching his daughter's basketball team and the importance of watching children discover their passions. He highlights how Title IX has paved the way for equal education, including in sports, and shares the story of basketball coach Pat Summitt. Obama emphasizes that girls who play sports are more likely to excel in school and graduate from college. He also emphasizes that Title IX goes beyond sports and addresses issues like inequality in math and science education and preventing sexual assault on campus. Obama expresses his commitment to keeping Title IX strong and ensuring equal opportunities for all children.